                     <origDate notBefore="1850" notAfter="1902">According to Additio 2, the Ms. was
                        donated to the church of ʾIyasus in 1894 year of mercy (= 1901/02
                        A.D.).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The name of the original donor(s) was
                     probably written in the erased part of Additio 1 and in the supplication
                     formulas throughout the Ms. 
 According to Additio 2, Za-Śǝllāse donated
                     the Ms. to the church of ʾIyasus (Gʷaḥgot) in 1901/02. His name and the name of
                     his wife Walatta Rufāʾel are also written in the supplication formulas, over
                     the erased name(s), in the same hand as Additio 2 (e.g., 7ra, 32ra). Two other names, &lt;...&gt; Mikāʾel and his wife
                     Ṣädalä Māryām, are added in some supplication formulas, in another secondary
                     hand (e.g., 25ra, 37va).</provenance></history>
